Cell.Text: Lot krongrah. You truly have the Voice of a dovah. Alduin's allies will think twice after this victory.

Node.Caption: MQ301PaarthurnaxIntroTopic: I defeated Alduin, but he escaped.

Cell.Text: [S] Yes... one of his allies could tell us. Motmahus... But it will not be so easy to... convince one of them to betray him. | Perhaps the hofkahsejun - the palace in Whiterun... Dragonsreach. It was originally built to house a captive dovah. | A fine place to trap one of Alduin's allies, hmm?

Node.Caption: MQ301PaarthurnaxIntroA1: I need to find out where Alduin went.

Cell.Text: Ni liivrah hin moro. True, this is not the final krongrah - victory. But not even the heroes of old were able to defeat Alduin in open battle. | Alduin always was pahlok - arrogant in his power. Uznahgar paar. He took domination as his birthright. | This should shake the loyalty of the dov who serve him.

Node.Caption: MQ301PaarthurnaxIntroA2: It wasn't really a victory, since Alduin escaped.

Cell.Text: [S] Hmm, yes. But your su'um is strong. I do not doubt that you can convince him of the need.

Node.Caption: MQ301PaarthurnaxIntroB1: The Jarl of Whiterun might not think so.

Cell.Text: I need your help. I need to trap a dragon in your palace.
[S] S|I must have misheard you. I thought you asked me to help you trap a dragon in my palace.
I need your help. I need to trap a dragon in your palace.
<<Shared>> What you're asking for is insane. Impossible! | You want me to let a dragon into the heart of my city, with the threat of war on my doorstep?
I need your help. I need to trap a dragon in your palace.
<<Shared>> What you're asking for is insane. Impossible! | Why would I agree to let a dragon into the heart of my city, after working so hard to keep them out?

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlDragonsreachTopic: I need your help trapping a dragon in Dragonsreach.

Cell.Text: What do you think the Imperials would be doing while this dragon is busy slaughtering my men?
Do you think the Stormcloaks will sit idle while this dragon is slaughtering my men and burning down my city?
Ulfric and General Tullius are both just waiting for me to make a wrong move. | Do you think they will sit idle while a dragon is slaughtering my men and burning my city?

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlDragonsreachB1

Cell.Text: No. I can't risk weakening the city while we are under the threat of enemy attack. I'm sorry.

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlDragonsreachB2

Cell.Text: [S] Then I would be glad to help you with your mad dragon-trapping scheme. | But getting both sides to agree to a truce will be difficult at this point. The bitterness has gone too deep. | Maybe... hmm... what of the Greybeards? They are respected by all Nords. High Hrothgar is neutral territory. | If the Greybeards were willing to host a peace council... then maybe Ulfric and Tullius would have to listen.

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlDragonsreachC1: What if you didn't have to worry about an enemy attack?

Cell.Text: Yes. This was ages ago, you understand. There were more of us then. Before the bruniikke - the Akaviri - came and killed all my zeymah. | I used to visit him from time to time. Nearly crazed by loneliness and captivity. Tiiraz sivaas. He did not even remember his own name. | I do not know how he came to be caught. But the bronjun... the Jarl... was very proud of his pet. Paak! | The hofkahsejun has been known as Dragonsreach ever since.

According to legend. Although I never thought to put the tale to the test. | Jarl Olaf One-Eye it was, who later became High King. | They say he Shouted it into submission in single combat atop Mount Anthor and brought it back to Whiterun. | Numinex was the dragon's name. That's his skull decorating the main hall.

Node.Caption: MQ301DragonsreachTopic: Dragonsreach was built to hold a dragon?

Cell.Text: Now that it's upon us, I'm rather looking forward to the challenge. I'll be famouser than Olaf One-Eye!

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlDragonsreachNotYet: Not quite yet.

Cell.Text: [S] G|My men know what to do. Make sure you do your part. I'm putting my city in your hands.

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlDragonsreachReady: I'm ready. Let's go trap a dragon.

Cell.Text: Zu'u bonaar. You went to a great deal of trouble to put me in this... humiliating position. | Hind siiv Alduin, hmm? No doubt you want to know where to find Alduin?

Node.Caption: MQ301OdahviingIntroTopic: How does it feel to be my prisoner?

Cell.Text: Rinik vazah. An apt phrase. Alduin bovul. One reason I came to your call was to test your thu'um for myself. | Many of us have begun to question Alduin's lordship, whether his thu'um was truly the strongest. | Among ourselves, of course. Mu ni meyye. None were yet ready to openly defy him.

Node.Caption: MQ301OdahviingB1: That's right. Where is he hiding?

Cell.Text: Unslaad krosis. Innumerable pardons. I digress. | He has travelled to Sovngarde to regain his strength, devouring the sillesejoor... the souls of the mortal dead. A privilege he jealously guards... | His door to Sovngarde is at Skuldafn, one of his ancient fanes high in the eastern mountains. | Mindoraan, pah ok middovahhe lahvraan til. I surely do not need to warn you that all his remaining strength is marshalled there. | Zu'u lost ofan hin laan... now that I have answered your question, you will allow me to go free?

Node.Caption: MQ301OdahviingB2: You were telling me where to find Alduin?

Cell.Text: Aam? Serve you? ...no. Ni tiid. If and when you defeat Alduin, I will reconsider. | Hmm... krosis. There is one... detail about Skuldafn I neglected to mention.

Node.Caption: MQ301OdahviingC1: Do you promise to serve me?

Cell.Text: Ah. Well. Hmm... krosis. There is one... detail about Skuldafn I neglected to mention.

Node.Caption: MQ301OdahviingC2: Not until Alduin is defeated.

Cell.Text: [S] Only this. You have the thu'um of a dovah, but without the wings of one, you will never set foot in Skuldafn. | Of course... I could fly you there. But not while imprisoned like this.

Node.Caption: MQ301OdahviingD1: Tell me what you know, then.

Cell.Text: G|Indeed. Orin brit ro. I cannot leave here until you defeat Alduin, which you cannot do without my help.

Node.Caption: MQ301OdahviingE1: We seem to be at an impasse, then.

Cell.Text: G|Ahraan. You wound me, Dovahkiin. I may not tell the whole truth, but I am no liar. | Go and see for yourself. Zu'u ni bo nol het. I willl be here... unless Alduin returns before you do.

Node.Caption: MQ301OdahviingE2: Do you expect me to take your word for that?

Cell.Text: Our plan worked.
[S] I admit, I doubted you, but no more. You've made a dragon submit to your will. A feat to rival the legendary Olaf One-Eye! What glory!
G|Lure it into the trap! I'm counting on you!
G|Do whatever you're going to do before it kills us all!
G|My men are ready. Now it's up to you.
G|Come, my men stand ready on the great porch.
G|Let's do this. Summon this dragon of yours.
G|This was your crazy idea, huh?
G|You better know what you're doing.
G|I don't know how you talked the Jarl into this.
G|Let's get this over with.

Node.Caption: MQ301DragonAttackBlockingTopic

Cell.Text: [S] G|<<Shared>> Onikaan koraav gein miraad. It is wise to recognize when you only have one choice. | And you can trust me. Zu'u ni tahrodiis. Alduin has proven himself unworthy to rule. I go my own way now. | Free me, and I will carry you to Skuldafn.

Node.Caption: MQ301OdahviingE3: Fine. I'll set you free if you promise to take me to Skuldafn.

Cell.Text: S|Alduin? The World-Eater himself? But... how can we fight him? Doesn't his return mean it's the end times?
How can we fight Alduin? Doesn't his return mean it's the end times?

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlAlduinReturnTopic: The threat is worse than you know. Alduin has returned.

Cell.Text: I didn't say anything about giving up.

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlAlduinReturnA1: It's only hopeless if we give up.

Cell.Text: I don't know about such things, but I heard the Greybeards summon you. That's good enough for me.

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlAlduinReturnA2: I'm Dragonborn. It's my destiny to stop him.

Cell.Text: Spoken like a true Nord. I'll stand beside you, Dragonborn.
No Nord could have said it better! I'll stand beside you, Dragonborn.

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlAlduinReturnA3: Maybe so, but I plan to go down fighting. What about you?

Cell.Text: Now, what's this nonsense about trapping a dragon in my palace?

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlTrapDragonTopic: I need your help.

Cell.Text: I want to help you, Dragonborn. And I will. But I need your help first.

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlTrapDragonA1: It's the only way to find Alduin before it's too late.

Cell.Text: Aye, Dragonborn. Maybe you can stop the dragons - and this war into the bargain.

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlArrangeTruceTopic: Leave that to me. I'll talk to Arngeir about hosting a peace council.

Cell.Text: [S] Then... Whiterun will stand with you, Dragonborn. We will take the risk, and gain the glory, whether it be in victory or defeat! | So what's the plan, then? How do you intend to lure a dragon into the trap?

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlReadyToTrapTopic: It's the only way to find Alduin before it's too late.

Cell.Text: As I promised, my men stand ready. The great chains are oiled. We wait on your word.
We'll be ready, don't worry. You do have a plan for actually luring a dragon into this trap, don't you?
My men will be ready when you are, Dragonborn. You have a truce to arrange first, eh?

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlWaitingForPlayerTopic: Are you ready to spring the trap on the dragon?

Cell.Text: Oh... well, I'll leave that to you. I trust you know your business. | Probably for the best. It will give me time to see if that old trap still works - and break the news to the men.

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlReadyToTrapA1: I don't know yet. But I know some people who can probably help.

Cell.Text: <<Shared>> What you're asking for is insane. Impossible! | You want me to let a dragon into the heart of my city, with the threat of war on my doorstep?
<<Shared>> What you're asking for is insane. Impossible! | Why would I agree to let a dragon into the heart of my city, after working so hard to keep them out?

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlDragonsreachA1: You heard right. It's the only way to stop the dragons.

Cell.Text: [S] Of course. You already saved Whiterun from that dragon. I owe you a great deal. | But I don't understand. Why let a dragon into the heart of my city when we've been working so hard to keep them out?
I'm sorry, but I can't do it. We'll just have to keep fighting the dragons as best we can.

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlDragonsreachA2: You know I wouldn't ask if it wasn't important. (Persuade)

Cell.Text: There must be another way. The risk is too great.

Node.Caption: MQ301JarlDragonsreachA3: It's the only way to stop the dragon attacks.
